00:36:36.770 --> 00:36:38.670
One-- I love this.

00:36:38.670 --> 00:36:41.060
One, it keeps out all light.

00:36:41.060 --> 00:36:43.560
So you're not going to get that
Heineken problem, especially

00:36:43.560 --> 00:36:46.140
with so many hoppy beers
being made these days.

00:36:46.140 --> 00:36:49.200
When you put a beer
in brown glass,

00:36:49.200 --> 00:36:52.120
it doesn't let light through
as much as green glass.

00:36:52.120 --> 00:36:56.160
So this is why most craft
brewers use brown glass.

00:36:56.160 --> 00:36:58.049
Clear glass is
absolutely the worst

00:36:58.049 --> 00:37:00.090
because it lets the most
amount of light through,

00:37:00.090 --> 00:37:01.890
so your beer will
skunk really fast.

00:37:01.890 --> 00:37:04.740
Green it'll skunk
less fast, but still.

00:37:04.740 --> 00:37:07.260
And brown, it'll take
just a little bit longer.

00:37:07.260 --> 00:37:09.210
Cans let no light through.

00:37:09.210 --> 00:37:10.600
That's first and foremost.

00:37:10.600 --> 00:37:13.150
It's also lighter packaging.

00:37:13.150 --> 00:37:14.880
They're easier to transport.

00:37:14.880 --> 00:37:15.930
They're easier to pack.

00:37:15.930 --> 00:37:17.640
They're easier to stack.

