00:46:44.310 --> 00:46:46.260
even here at Google--

00:46:46.260 --> 00:46:48.300
sexism in beer.

00:46:48.300 --> 00:46:50.460
One of our beers today
from Three Weavers

00:46:50.460 --> 00:46:52.110
is a female-owned brewery.

00:46:52.110 --> 00:46:53.610
It's three women who own that.

00:46:53.610 --> 00:46:54.675
JOHN HOLL: Yep.

00:46:54.675 --> 00:46:56.133
KEVIN NELSON: Maybe
talk just a bit

00:46:56.133 --> 00:46:57.600
about kind of the
history of sexism

00:46:57.600 --> 00:47:00.330
in beer, and where
the industry is today.

00:47:00.330 --> 00:47:01.980
JOHN HOLL: It's getting better.

00:47:01.980 --> 00:47:04.050
It's getting better.

00:47:04.050 --> 00:47:07.107
For a long time, it was a
male-dominated industry,

00:47:07.107 --> 00:47:08.940
both in the people who
worked at the brewery

00:47:08.940 --> 00:47:11.260
and who owned the brewery.

00:47:11.260 --> 00:47:15.210
But beer itself as a
beverage doesn't know gender.

00:47:15.210 --> 00:47:16.230
It doesn't know sex.

00:47:16.230 --> 00:47:17.070
It doesn't know religion.

00:47:17.070 --> 00:47:17.986
It doesn't know creed.

00:47:17.986 --> 00:47:22.350
It doesn't know your
political beliefs, as it were.

00:47:22.350 --> 00:47:25.489
It's a great leveler
in a lot of ways.

00:47:25.489 --> 00:47:27.030
But when the beer
that was being made

00:47:27.030 --> 00:47:29.610
for a long time of the
beer-flavored beer,

00:47:29.610 --> 00:47:32.904
the American industrial
light lager, yeah,

00:47:32.904 --> 00:47:34.320
there's women who
drank it, but it

00:47:34.320 --> 00:47:35.740
wasn't being marketed to them.

00:47:35.740 --> 00:47:38.040
In fact, it was almost
being marketed against them,

00:47:38.040 --> 00:47:40.800
where you'd see Budweiser
commercials with women

00:47:40.800 --> 00:47:44.130
in bikinis being
objectified, and then

00:47:44.130 --> 00:47:46.725
the guys clinking their
glasses, being like, yeah.

00:47:46.725 --> 00:47:51.480
And these days, you walk into a
tap room like at Three Weavers,

00:47:51.480 --> 00:47:55.470
and it's diverse.

00:47:55.470 --> 00:47:57.330
People are coming
for the good beer.

00:47:57.330 --> 00:47:59.550
And they can come
from the tech sector,

00:47:59.550 --> 00:48:02.760
or they can drive an Uber,
or they can be a reporter,

00:48:02.760 --> 00:48:04.257
or they can be whatever.

00:48:04.257 --> 00:48:06.090
And they're all coming
in for the same beer.

00:48:06.090 --> 00:48:08.370
And it's sort of this
great leveler for us.

00:48:08.370 --> 00:48:11.100
And so yeah, sexism still
exists in the industry.

00:48:11.100 --> 00:48:12.870
And I get into it
in the book where

00:48:12.870 --> 00:48:14.411
there's some breweries
that have done

00:48:14.411 --> 00:48:18.270
some really boneheaded things,
some really stupid things.

00:48:18.270 --> 00:48:21.930
Naming their beers that
seemingly promote rape culture,

00:48:21.930 --> 00:48:25.230
or that are xenophobic,
or homophobic,

00:48:25.230 --> 00:48:29.400
or anything else in between.

00:48:29.400 --> 00:48:31.530
And if you're doing that
and you're a brewer,

00:48:31.530 --> 00:48:33.750
get the hell out
of the industry.

00:48:33.750 --> 00:48:35.190
Just, like, stop.

00:48:35.190 --> 00:48:36.460
We don't need it.

00:48:36.460 --> 00:48:38.550
We don't want it.

00:48:38.550 --> 00:48:41.640
But I think that consumers
are speaking up now more

00:48:41.640 --> 00:48:43.239
and more thanks to technology.

00:48:43.239 --> 00:48:45.030
And there's a lot of
cool things that exist

00:48:45.030 --> 00:48:46.196
between beer and technology.

00:48:46.196 --> 00:48:49.920
But if somebody posts something
on Facebook, and they're like,

00:48:49.920 --> 00:48:53.700
hey, we've named this beer, and
it's this really idiotic name,

00:48:53.700 --> 00:48:58.200
it whips around the world
so fast with smart people

00:48:58.200 --> 00:49:00.450
being like, knock this off.

00:49:00.450 --> 00:49:02.130
Like, this is wrong.

00:49:02.130 --> 00:49:03.840
And you can almost
set an egg timer

00:49:03.840 --> 00:49:06.430
to when the apology
is going to happen.

00:49:06.430 --> 00:49:09.690
And I think that that's
great, because it keeps people

00:49:09.690 --> 00:49:12.270
in check, and it
sort of hopefully

00:49:12.270 --> 00:49:15.810
drives that culture underground
enough so that it eventually

00:49:15.810 --> 00:49:16.770
just disappears.

00:49:16.770 --> 00:49:19.562
Because we don't
need it in our world.

